From: Hans Verkuil <hverkuil-cisco@xs4all.nl>
Date: Thu, 2 May 2024 13:38:42 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] media: cec: cec-api: add locking in cec_release()
Message-ID: <e5a57815b34e85d7c338841d5c17097afe235f38.1714649924.git.hverkuil-cisco@xs4all.nl>
Patch-mainline: Submitted, linux-media ML
References: CVE-2024-23848 bsc#1219104

When cec_release() uses fh->msgs it has to take fh->lock,
otherwise the list can get corrupted.

Signed-off-by: Hans Verkuil <hverkuil-cisco@xs4all.nl>
Reported-by: Yang, Chenyuan <cy54@illinois.edu>
Fixes: ca684386e6e2 ("[media] cec: add HDMI CEC framework (api)")
Closes: https://lore.kernel.org/linux-media/PH7PR11MB57688E64ADE4FE82E658D86DA09EA@PH7PR11MB5768.namprd11.prod.outlook.com/
Acked-by: Takashi Iwai <tiwai@suse.de>

---
 drivers/media/cec/core/cec-api.c |    3 +++
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+)

--- a/drivers/media/cec/core/cec-api.c
+++ b/drivers/media/cec/core/cec-api.c
@@ -678,6 +678,8 @@ static int cec_release(struct inode *ino
 		list_del(&data->xfer_list);
 	}
 	mutex_unlock(&adap->lock);
+
+	mutex_lock(&fh->lock);
 	while (!list_empty(&fh->msgs)) {
 		struct cec_msg_entry *entry =
 			list_first_entry(&fh->msgs, struct cec_msg_entry, list);
@@ -695,6 +697,7 @@ static int cec_release(struct inode *ino
 			kfree(entry);
 		}
 	}
+	mutex_unlock(&fh->lock);
 	kfree(fh);
 
 	cec_put_device(devnode);
